- [ ] [P2] [feature] Panel layout persistence — remember the last-active sub-view (`terminals` / `explore` / `mdns` / `topology` / `todo`) per window and restore on next `activate`. Stored alongside the audit log, but keyed off `workbench.view.extension.superset`. — [plans/2026-07-05-architecture-panel-layout-persistence.md](plans/2026-07-05-architecture-panel-layout-persistence.md)
- [ ] [P2] [chore] `Superset: Show Diagnostics` webview — one-click snapshot of every subsystem (terminals / mDNS / topology / todo / engines / activation session), with Copy-to-clipboard and Save-to-file buttons. Complements the existing `superset.showLogs` (time-series log) with a structured "now" view, unblocks GitHub-issue triage. See scan note 2026-06-24#6A. — [plans/2026-06-24-chore-show-diagnostics-webview.md](plans/2026-06-24-chore-show-diagnostics-webview.md)
